# 🚀 Spring Boot Concepts Roadmap

---

## 🌱 BASIC (Foundation – Must Know)

### 🔹 Spring & Spring Boot Core
- What is Spring Framework
- What is Spring Boot
- Spring vs Spring Boot
- Auto-configuration
- Starter dependencies

### 🔹 Project Setup
- Spring Initializr
- Maven / Gradle basics
- Project structure (main class, packages)

### 🔹 Core Concepts
- Inversion of Control (IoC)
- Dependency Injection (DI)
- Beans
- Application Context

### 🔹 Annotations (Core)
- @SpringBootApplication
- @Component
- @Service
- @Repository
- @Autowired

### 🔹 Web Basics (REST APIs)
- REST architecture
- @RestController
- @RequestMapping
- @GetMapping, @PostMapping, etc.
- @PathVariable
- @RequestParam

### 🔹 Request Handling
- DTOs (Data Transfer Objects)
- JSON request/response
- @RequestBody
- @ResponseBody

---

## ⚙️ INTERMEDIATE (Job-Ready Backend)

### 🗄️ Database & Persistence
- Spring Data JPA
- Hibernate ORM
- @Entity, @Table
- @Id, @GeneratedValue
- Relationships:
  - OneToOne
  - OneToMany
  - ManyToOne
  - ManyToMany
- JpaRepository
- CRUD operations

### ⚠️ Exception Handling
- Global exception handling
- @ControllerAdvice
- Custom exceptions

### ✅ Validation
- @Valid
- Bean Validation (Hibernate Validator)
- Custom validations

### ⚙️ Configuration
- application.properties / application.yml
- Profiles (dev, prod)
- Environment variables

### 📦 Logging
- Logging basics
- Log levels (INFO, DEBUG, ERROR)
- SLF4J / Logback

### 🔄 Data Processing
- Streams API usage in services
- DTO ↔ Entity mapping

### 🔌 API Design Best Practices
- Layered architecture:
  - Controller → Service → Repository
- Clean code practices

---

## 🚀 ADVANCED (Production Level)

### 🔐 Security
- Spring Security
- Authentication & Authorization
- JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
- Role-based access

### 🧩 Microservices
- Monolith vs Microservices
- Service-to-service communication
- Feign Client / REST clients

### 🌐 API Gateway
- Routing
- Load balancing
- Rate limiting

### 🔄 Interceptors & Filters
- Request filtering
- Logging/interception

### ⚡ Performance & Caching
- @Cacheable
- Redis (optional)

### 🐳 Deployment & DevOps
- Docker
- CI/CD basics
- JAR packaging

### 🧪 Testing
- JUnit
- Mockito
- @SpringBootTest
- Integration testing

### 📡 Messaging
- Kafka / RabbitMQ

### 🔍 Monitoring & Observability
- Spring Boot Actuator
- Metrics & health checks

---

## 🧭 Learning Flow

1. BASIC → Build simple REST API  
2. INTERMEDIATE → Add DB, validation, exceptions  
3. ADVANCED → Security, scaling, deployment  

---

## 💡 Notes

- BASIC = Foundation (mandatory)
- INTERMEDIATE = Most real-world work
- ADVANCED = Needed for scaling & top-level roles
